title: Utah Beginning Racers Program
description:
Series of five USAC clinics held on three consecutive Wednesdays in April (13th, 20th and 27th). The clinics are open to all male, female and junior riders. Male riders completing all five clinics will receive enough points to upgrade from Cat 5 to Cat 4. Female riders will receive 10 out of 20 points required to upgrade to Cat 3. All riders wanted to use points to upgrade must have a current USAC racing license. 
The clinics will run from 6-8pm at Lagoon in Farmington, UT. Rider check-in starts at 5:30.
Pricing for all 5 clinics: Men $125, Women- $50, Juniors- $50

title: Wasatch 360
description: A 6hr mountain bike race with Solo, Duo and Trio categories benefitting the Summit Bike Club, a non-profit organization focusing on junior with a mission to educate athletes about the skills, safety and sportsmanship of cycling.
directions: Race base is located off Coyote Lane, 1 mile north of Heber City and 1 mile south of the UVU campus. After about .3 miles on the paved road heading east, turn left onto the dirt road. Flags and signs will be setup to help with direction.

title: Huntsman 140
description: The 2016 Huntsman 140 is a fundraising road cycling event finishing in the afternoon of Saturday, June 18, 2016 near Huntsman Cancer Institute in Salt Lake City, Utah. All funds raised through this one-day ride go to Huntsman Cancer Foundation (HCF) to support cancer research at the Huntsman Cancer Institute (HCI). This ride is ideal for cyclists of all levels--from avid riders taking on the 140-mile challenge to newer pedalers enjoying the rolling 25-mile course (the ride includes 28, 54, 75, and 140 mile options). Each rider is encouraged to fundraise $500 for cancer research at HCI.
course:
The Huntsman 140 includes four distance/five course options, which are:
1. 140-mile Delta, UT to Salt Lake City, UT point-to-point
2. 140-mile Salt Lake City, UT out-and-back
3. 75-mile Salt Lake City, UT out-and-back
4. 54-mile Salt Lake City, UT out-and-back
5. 28-mile Salt Lake City, UT out-and-back
notes: The Huntsman 140 is a non-competitive Fun Ride.
directions: Course maps and event directions will be available online at http://huntsman140.com

Cache Gran Fondo
description: 50 and 100 mile gran fondo.  Start at Logan Regional Hospital and finish in downtown Logan on a closed-off city street  (100N Main).  5th annual event.
course: Same as in past; 100 miler Logan to Trenton to Weston, ID, to Malad, to Riverside, UT, to Mendon and end in downtown Logan.  50 miler: Logan to Trenton, Trenton the Clarkston to Newton to Mendon, finish in downtown Logan.
notes: The Cache Gran Fondo is an annual Italian-style ride in Cache Valley in Northern Utah. The ride is not officially timed, however there is an digital race clock at the start and finish of the race so all riders can test their ride time. The Cache Gran Fondo occurs on the 2nd Saturday of every July and riders can ride either on a 50-mile or 100-mile route. Proceeds from the 2013 and 2014 ride went toward accomplishing a goal to fund breast cancer screenings for uninsured women who live in Cache Valley, and in 2015, a percentage of the proceeds will be donated to the Logan Regional Hospital Foundation to continue to fund this special service.
directions: There are plenty of places to park at the start and finish line. Please note that the finish line is about 10 blocks away from the start line. Please enter parking areas by driving east until you get to 600 East. 400 East will be closed off to vehicles on race day morning!

LOTOJA CLASSIC

address.city: LOGAN, UT TO JACKSON HOLE, WY

description: 2016 LoToJa Classic RR -- Saturday, September 10 will mark the 34th edition of the Logan to Jackson bicycle classic road race (and non-competitive ride). LoToJa has grown from a small group of seven college friends to an event that reaches its rider cap on the same day registration opens.  At 206 miles, LoToJa is the longest one-day USAC-sanctioned bicycle race in the United States.  LoToJa participants must conquer three mountain passes (climbing almost 10,000 feet), as they pedal their bikes through the scenic countryside of Utah, Idaho, and Wyoming. Visit lotojaclassic.com for more event information.

title: Huntsman World Senior Games
description: This 5K hill climb event in part of the Huntsman World Senior Games held in St. George, Utah.  It is open to participants 50+ years.
course: The course runs up Snow Canyon State Park in Ivins, Utah, a scenic and colorful canyon.  It contains uphill rollies 4% to 8%; short sections 10% to 11%.
registration: Registration begins March 1, 2016 and ends September 1, 2016 at our website, www.seniorgames.net.
notes: Medals will be awarded in 5-year age increments.
directions: Huntsman World Senior Games takes place in St. George, Utah. Course maps and the Official Cycling Race Bible are available on the Cycling page of our website -- www.seniorgames.net.
